Are we switching to Brontouring? Comment for links 🔗 but read the full review below ⏬

In frame: @elfcosmetics Camo Liquid Bronzer & Contour

Mini Review:

Travel friendly packaging with a doe foot applicator. 

Beginner-friendly? Yes!
But since it’s packed with pigment, I recommend blending some on the back of your hand first before applying to the face, it gives better control and prevents pigment overload.

They do dry down quickly, but you still get enough time to blend-fair enough, IMO.
No patches over makeup and feels super lightweight on the skin.

I’ve been using Tan (neutral olive undertone – perfect Brontour shade) and Tan Deep (leans orange – warmer Brontour shade).
For my medium warm skin tone, both work more as Brontouring shades.

So what is Brontouring?
It’s a makeup technique that combines bronzing + contouring — warming up the face while softly sculpting it at the same time.
It usually involves a cool-toned or neutral bronzer that gives you structure without harsh lines.

✅ Best for:
-Soft-sculpted, everyday makeup looks.
-Medium to tan skin tones, where grey-toned contours can look ashy.
-Those who skip traditional contouring but still want definition + warmth.

Since I rarely contour separately, having Brontour-friendly shades like these makes my routine quicker and more natural-looking.

If you’re looking for true contouring, e.l.f. also has deeper cool or neutral-toned shades ideal for deeper skin tones.

In frame: @diambeauty Draw Me In Lip Marker

-Pointed tip makes it easy to line or fill in—zero hassle.
-Feels lightweight and breathable on the lips.
-The shades I swatched here on myself are well pigmented and can be layered too for more opaque pigment, however the other shades need more layering as compared to these deeper shades. 

-The deeper shade from the range: Mark my words and Taupe line does last a long time, others didn’t last that longer. 

In my opinion, these work best as lip liners when you’re wearing lipstick, especially because traditional lip liners tend to fade quickly and aren’t usually smudge-proof.
But when I’m just layering a lip balm, I prefer removing it slightly for a soft, smudged tint across the lips—you can even smudge it with fingers during application, it looks much more natural that way. Since I don’t have pigmented lips, using it only as a lip liner leaves an odd-looking gap, so this technique works better for me.

You do you, depending on what suits your lips best!

A word of caution: If you have dry or chapped lips, avoid filling them in completely with this—it can settle into the lines and won’t look very flattering. 

So the exact shade dupe to Sacheu Beauty Peel Off Lip Liner Stain in the shade 03 P-Inked is @diambeauty Lip Marker in the shade Mark my words.

Wearing: @discover.pilgrim Glitter Lipstick With Matte Finish – Shade: Khalifa 02

Not usually a fan of glitter on the lips, but this one hits differently.
From the luxe golden packaging to the one-swipe color payoff that covers even two-toned lips – this lipstick glides on like butter and settles into a comfortable, non-drying matte finish.

The glitter is subtle yet stunning – no chunky feel, just a soft shine that makes lips look plump and pretty.
If you love a glittery pout without the fuss, this is a total must-try.
